{
  "texts": [
    "Discriminative fragments are obtained through the two methods discussed in this section: multi-instance learning and direct localization.",
    "In addition, two common challenges in weakly supervised learning are discussed: complete action modeling and action-context separation.",
    "Multi-instance learning (MIL) is a form of weakly supervised learning.",
    "The training instances are arranged in groups, called bags, and provide labels for the entire bag.",
    "Supervision is provided only for the complete set of products, and no separate labels are provided for the instances contained in the bag."
  ]
}